quran[21]{c,v,t}:
  44,19,"And don’t exalt (yourselves) against Allah. Truly, I have come to you with a clear authority"
  44,20,"And truly, I seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord, lest you stone me"
  44,21,"But if you don’t believe me, then keep away from me and leave me alone.”"
  44,22,"So he (Moses) called upon (when they were aggressive) his Lord (saying) indeed: “These are criminal people.”"
  44,23,"(Allah said): “You depart with My servants by night. Surely, you will be pursued"
  44,24,"And (when you have crossed the sea with your people), then leave the sea as it is (quiet and divided). Surely, they are a host to be drowned.”"
  44,25,How many gardens and springs did they (Pharaoh’s people) leave behind
  44,26,and corn-fields and goodly places
  44,27,and comforts (of life) they used to take delight in it
  44,28,Thus We made other people inherit them (the children of Israel inherit the kingdom of Egypt)
  44,29,"And neither the heavens and the earth did weep for them, nor were they given a respite"
  44,30,And indeed We saved the children of Israel from the humiliating punishment
  44,31,from Pharaoh. Surely! He was arrogant and was one of the transgressors
  44,32,"and surely, We chose them (the children of Israel) above the worlds (during the time of Moses) with knowledge"
  44,33,And granted them signs in which there was a plain trial
  44,34,"Surely, these (people of Quraish) say"
  44,35,“There is nothing after our first death and we shall not be resurrected
  44,36,Bring back our forefathers if you speak the truth!”
  44,37,Are they better than the people of Tubba and those who were before them? We destroyed them because they were indeed criminals
  44,38,"And We did not create the heavens and the earth, and all that is between them, for merely a play"
  44,39,"We have not created them but (to reveal) the truth, but most of them don’t know"